{"id": "EUVD-2025-20807", "enisaUuid": "7c81b930-3222-3c2c-b310-c2eb9fb86894", "description": "In the Linux kernel, the following vulnerability has been resolved:\n\ndrm/amd/display: Add sanity checks for drm_edid_raw()\n\nWhen EDID is retrieved via drm_edid_raw(), it doesn't guarantee to\nreturn proper EDID bytes the caller wants: it may be either NULL (that\nleads to an Oops) or with too long bytes over the fixed size raw_edid\narray (that may lead to memory corruption).  The latter was reported\nactually when connected with a bad adapter.\n\nAdd sanity checks for drm_edid_raw() to address the above corner\ncases, and return EDID_BAD_INPUT accordingly.\n\n(cherry picked from commit 648d3f4d209725d51900d6a3ed46b7b600140cdf)", "datePublished": "2025-07-09T12:31:35", "dateUpdated": "2025-11-19T21:31:15", "baseScore": 0.0, "references": ["https://git.kernel.org/stable/c/4b63507d7cd243574753c6b91f68516d9103f1de", "https://git.kernel.org/stable/c/6847b3b6e84ef37451c074e6a8db3fbd250c8dbf", "https://nvd.nist.gov/vuln/detail/CVE-2025-38254"], "aliases": ["CVE-2025-38254"], "assigner": "Linux", "epss": 0.02, "enisaIdProduct": [{"id": "0fcc1ece-e57a-3aa6-a2a2-622ee47803c4", "product": {"name": "Linux"}, "product_version": "48edb2a4256eedf6c92eecf2bc7744e6ecb44b5e <4b63507d7cd243574753c6b91f68516d9103f1de"}, {"id": "108d62bb-a384-3eaf-a886-c130cfe9b67d", "product": {"name": "Linux"}, "product_version": "patch: 6.15.5"}, {"id": "1a5f1e33-5bf3-3ee9-9419-94e8b4017830", "product": {"name": "Linux"}, "product_version": "patch: 6.16"}, {"id": "2b6581c4-72b3-355d-ba59-d4f233498704", "product": {"name": "Linux"}, "product_version": "patch: 6.16-rc4"}, {"id": "904cf810-b7ff-322d-b634-e43b8388e996", "product": {"name": "Linux"}, "product_version": "6.13"}, {"id": "d762dd86-3f84-37d0-9e97-f0213269061e", "product": {"name": "Linux"}, "product_version": "48edb2a4256eedf6c92eecf2bc7744e6ecb44b5e <6847b3b6e84ef37451c074e6a8db3fbd250c8dbf"}, {"id": "fea9f77a-f893-3a89-b92e-66bd541a4777", "pr